                {
                    "content": "<script type=\"text/javascript\">\n    var problem_name = 'aplusbplusc';\n</script>\n\n<p><b>Now it's your turn.</b> Write a program that reads <i>three</i> numbers from its input and prints their sum:\n\n<div id=\"visualizer\"></div>\n\n<pre class=\"input\" style=\"display: none\">2\n3\n6</pre>\n\n<div style=\"display: none;\" id=\"awesome\"><b>Awesome, you did it!</b> How about trying <a href=\"/lessons/print_input_numbers/problems/area_of_right_triangle/\">the next problem</a>?</div>",
