        {
            "title": "Why do I learn programming?",
            "blocks": [
                {
                    "content": "<p><b>Programming improves your life.</b>\nWhatever you do in your life, you can start hacking it right away.\n<ul>\n    <li><b>Scientists</b> collect and process data using programs to do research\n    <li><b>Illustrators and musicians</b> automate daily routines using scripts\n    <li><b>Students</b> can get a very well-paid job in months. Just look at the salaries of\n    Software Engineers at Glassdoor\n</ul>",
                    "type": "html"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "title": "Why do I learn Python?",
            "blocks": [
                {
                    "content": "<p>Python is a great choice whether it's your first or next programming language.\n<ul>\n    <li><b>Python is very easy and flexible.</b> The programs in Python are tinier than in other languages.\n    <li><b>Powerful.</b> Due to its huge community Python is very popular as a server-side language. Google (spider, search engine, Google Maps), Netflix and Pinterest\n    use it a lot. Youtube, Quora, Reddit, Dropbox, Yahoo, Battlefield 2, Civilization 4, NASA, AlphaGene &mdash; all of them use Python; see the entire list <a href=\"https://wiki.python.org/moin/OrganizationsUsingPython\">here</a>.\n    <li><b>High demand for programmers.</b> See open job positions on <a href=\"https://careers.stackoverflow.com/jobs?searchTerm=python\">StackOverflow</a>",
                    "type": "html"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "title": "What websites/apps are coded in Python?",
            "blocks": [
                {
                    "content": "<p>Python is a great choice whether it's your first or next programming language. Here's the list of few projects/organizations that use Python: \n<ul>\n    <li>Google, Netflix and Pinterest\n    use it a lot. Youtube, Quora, Reddit, Dropbox, Google Maps. Yahoo, Battlefield 2, Civilization 4, NASA, AlphaGene &mdash; all of them use Python; see the entire list <a href=\"https://wiki.python.org/moin/OrganizationsUsingPython\">here</a>.",
                    "type": "html"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "title": "Okay, how to learn Python?",
            "blocks": [
                {
                    "content": "<p>There is a ton of way to do this, really. You can read books, or you can watch Youtube videos.\nHowever, <b>you better solve coding problems</b>, as you should start thinking like a programmer &mdash; and\nthis skill comes with hard work.\n\n<p style=\"font-size: 30px;\">Ready?\n<button class=\"snakify-button-start\">Jump to the first lesson</button>\n<script>\n$(function() {\n    $('.snakify-button-start').click(function() {\n        location.href = 'https://snakify.org/lessons/print_input_numbers/';\n    });\n});\n</script>\n</p>",
                    "type": "html"
                }
